g.text: Signal Handling Architecture Pitfall (Async) vs. Solution (Sync) [signal.c]

ol.li: Kernel picks a random thread to deliver signal.
Handler runs on Thread 2 stack, potentially calling unsafe printf or malloc.
Block First: Call pthread_sigmask in main() before any pthread_create.
Dedicated Waiter: One thread calls sigwait() in a loop. All others keep signals blocked.
Atomic Notification: Use a shutdown_flag protected by mutex + pthread_cond_broadcast.
Safe Exit: Workers check shutdown_flag after waking from cond_wait.
